headline: 'They shoot, arrest, extort. It's constant terror': In Sudan, the 'RSF State' as told by those who fled it
description: As the threat of Sudan being partitioned looms, the paramilitary Rapid Support Forces (RSF) claims it could govern Darfur. Those who have managed to escape describe a reign of tyranny and arbitrary rule.

description: A drop in the number of births can help reduce unemployment, ease housing pressure and improve the education system, argues Guillaume Duval, the former editor-in-chief of 'Alternatives économiques', in an op-ed for Le Monde.

headline: Epstein scandal deals new blow to Norway's crown princess
description: Newly unsealed files released this weekend exposed Crown Princess Mette-Marit's friendship with the sex offender Jeffrey Epstein. The timing could not be worse for Norway's royal palace: On Tuesday, Mette-Marit's 29-year-old son will go on trial to face charges of rape, assault and drug offenses.

headline: Infantino, Trump's compliant underling in the lead-up to the 2026 World Cup
description: As the threats of the US president run counter to the universal spirit of the 2026 FIFA World Cup, FIFA's president stands out for his complicit apathy, writes Alexandre Lemarié for Le Monde.

headline: France faces a crossfire of Russian and American disinformation
description: Since the start of the year, pro-Russian networks and Trump-aligned accounts have increasingly targeted France. While their methods differ, they pose an unprecedented challenge.
